All Christians will be the same.

47:10.690 --> 47:14.455
There is neither juvenile Gentile, barbarian or Scythian, bond nor free.

47:14.715 --> 47:25.010
The only thing that is different is that because of this peculiar relationship as the first of the natural branches, they are going to be grafting again.

47:26.562 --> 47:34.614
But remember that as regards the grafting, there is no difference between there being grafted in and the Gentiles being grafted in.

47:35.495 --> 47:42.586
It takes the same grace of God to convert a Jew as a Gentile and a Gentile as a Jew, and they will share the same blessings.

47:42.866 --> 47:48.114
They're all jointers of exactly the same promises and all the same blessing hooks.

47:48.695 --> 47:53.682
Well there, it seems to me, is the meaning of this olive tree.

47:54.594 --> 48:05.668
This picture that the Apostle puts before us here in the 17th chapter of this 17th verse of the 11th chapter of the mighty Epistle to the Romans.

48:05.749 --> 48:12.057
Now then, having said that he is in a position to address a certain appeal to the Gentiles.

48:12.117 --> 48:21.048
And I trust that next week, God willing, we shall see how it all now works out quite inevitably from this fundamental position.

48:21.529 --> 48:22.290
Let us pray.

48:23.394 --> 48:28.820
O Lord our God, we again thank thee for the mystery and the marvel of thy grace.

48:29.541 --> 48:36.768
O Lord, how can we as Gentiles thank thee sufficiently that thou hast ever grafted us into this olive tree?

48:37.189 --> 48:46.239
We thank thee equally, O God, that thou art going to deal with those first natural branches that thou hast cut off, that thou will graft them in again?

48:46.839 --> 48:52.946
We thank thee, O Lord, for the purposes of thy grace and for the glory of thy plan of redemption.

48:53.282 --> 48:56.767
Oh God, we pray thee, to increase our understanding.

48:57.167 --> 49:02.655
Help us to realize tonight, as we've never done before, that we are what we are by thy grace.

49:03.216 --> 49:07.902
There was done something contrary to nature, to us to bring us into such a position.

49:08.463 --> 49:13.269
We thank thee for the root and fatness of this blessed olive tree.

49:13.289 --> 49:22.482
We thank thee that we belong to the household of God, that we are thy children, that we are fellow citizens, with all the saints of all the centuries.

49:22.626 --> 49:27.193
We think that we have one blessed hook to which we look forward together.

49:27.233 --> 49:38.209
Oh God, we do indeed rejoice in our position as being among thy people, the covenant people of God.

49:38.970 --> 49:47.442
Oh Lord, grant that we may so realize that we shall ever be filled with a sense of wonder and of love and of praise.

49:47.554 --> 50:05.492
here as O Lord, and grant us thy blessing as we part from one another this night, and now may the grace of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, and the love of God and the fellowship and the communion of the Holy Spirit abide and continue with us.

50:05.972 --> 50:14.220
Now this night throughout the remainder of this hour short and certain earthly life in pilgrimage and evermore.

50:15.302 --> 50:15.762
Amen.

